<item>
  <title>Preferencias declaradas</title>
  <link>https://diezvariante.cl/blog/posts/iclv-1/iclv-1.html</link>
  <description><![CDATA[ 





<p>Bienvenido al blog. Este primer post muestra las capacidades básicas del formato.</p>
<section id="texto-y-listas" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="texto-y-listas">Texto y listas</h2>
<p>Puedes escribir en <strong>Markdown</strong> normal. Las listas funcionan como siempre:</p>
<ul>
<li>Punto uno</li>
<li>Punto dos</li>
<li>Punto tres</li>
</ul>
</section>
<section id="ecuaciones-con-latex" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="ecuaciones-con-latex">Ecuaciones con LaTeX</h2>
<p>Inline: la fórmula de Euler es <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?e%5E%7Bi%5Cpi%7D%20+%201%20=%200">.</p>
<p>Bloque centrado:</p>
<p><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%0A%5Cint_%7B-%5Cinfty%7D%5E%7B%5Cinfty%7D%20e%5E%7B-x%5E2%7D%20%5C,%20dx%20=%20%5Csqrt%7B%5Cpi%7D%0A"></p>
<p>Otra más:</p>
<p><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%0Af(x)%20=%20%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B%5Csigma%5Csqrt%7B2%5Cpi%7D%7D%20%5Cexp%5C!%5Cleft(-%5Cfrac%7B(x-%5Cmu)%5E2%7D%7B2%5Csigma%5E2%7D%5Cright)%0A"></p>
</section>
<section id="código" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="código">Código</h2>
<div class="code-copy-outer-scaffold"><div class="sourceCode" id="cb1" style="background: #f1f3f5;"><pre class="sourceCode python code-with-copy"><code class="sourceCode python"><span id="cb1-1"><span class="kw" style="color: #003B4F;
background-color: null;
font-weight: bold;
font-style: inherit;">def</span> fibonacci(n: <span class="bu" style="color: null;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">int</span>) <span class="op" style="color: #5E5E5E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">-&gt;</span> <span class="bu" style="color: null;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">list</span>[<span class="bu" style="color: null;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">int</span>]:</span>
<span id="cb1-2">    a, b <span class="op" style="color: #5E5E5E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">=</span> <span class="dv" style="color: #AD0000;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">0</span>, <span class="dv" style="color: #AD0000;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">1</span></span>
<span id="cb1-3">    result <span class="op" style="color: #5E5E5E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">=</span> []</span>
<span id="cb1-4">    <span class="cf" style="color: #003B4F;
background-color: null;
font-weight: bold;
font-style: inherit;">for</span> _ <span class="kw" style="color: #003B4F;
background-color: null;
font-weight: bold;
font-style: inherit;">in</span> <span class="bu" style="color: null;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">range</span>(n):</span>
<span id="cb1-5">        result.append(a)</span>
<span id="cb1-6">        a, b <span class="op" style="color: #5E5E5E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">=</span> b, a <span class="op" style="color: #5E5E5E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">+</span> b</span>
<span id="cb1-7">    <span class="cf" style="color: #003B4F;
background-color: null;
font-weight: bold;
font-style: inherit;">return</span> result</span>
<span id="cb1-8"></span>
<span id="cb1-9"><span class="bu" style="color: null;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">print</span>(fibonacci(<span class="dv" style="color: #AD0000;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">10</span>))</span></code></pre></div></div>
</section>
<section id="cita" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="cita">Cita</h2>
<blockquote class="blockquote">
<p>“La simplicidad es la sofisticación definitiva.” — Leonardo da Vinci</p>
</blockquote>


</section>

 ]]></description>
